15. Qd7{ All time allowing  bxc5 . }
16. h3
16. a5( { White can do some damage to our structure with }17.bxc5 { but we will hold the balance nonetheless. After }17...dxc5 { White has some weak points at  d3  and we will be able to create a passed pawn. }18.a4 b4⇆ {  Efimenko  had the better chances in  Anand  (2785) -  Efimenko  (2648), 1-0 (50), Dubai 2014. } )
