7. Bb3
7. d6
8. c3{ Making place for the bishop retreat to  c2 , in case of ... Na5 . }
8. O-O{ The main line. We will encounter a lot of transpositions of moves. In the bigger deal of the games, White will not rush but positionally improve his  b1 -knight in the typical Ruy Lopez knight manoeuvre  b1 - d2 - f1 - g3 / e3  (with the footprint of Fischer), play  h3  and then think about  d3 - d4 . In most of the lines, we follow the same plan of ... Na5 , ... c5  and ... Nc6 , with the footprint of Chigorin! }
9. Re1( 9.Nbd2 Na5 10.Bc2 c5 11.d4 Qc7 { . This position leads to the main line of the Chigorin, with the only difference being that White lost a tempo by playing  d3 - d4 . } )( 9.a4 Bd7 { would transpose to the   8.a4  chapter . } )
9. Na5{ This whole operation of ... Na5 , ... c5  and ... Nc6  takes time. In the meantime, White has to move his bishop back to a worse place ( c2 ). }
10. Bc2
10. c5{ The same approach as in the main lines. Black is expanding his territory on the queenside. }
11. Nbd2
11. Nc6{ The knight no longer has a role on  a5 . Time to move back towards the center. }
12. Nf1( 12.h3 Re8 13.Nf1 h6 14.Ng3 { transposes to  the main line . } )
12. h6{ It's always useful to take control over the  g5 -square. }
13. Ng3( 13.d4? { would be poorly timed: }13...cxd4 14.cxd4 { because of }14...Bg4!∓ { when White loses control over the  d4 -square. } )( 13.h3 Be6 14.Ng3 Re8 15.d4 cxd4 16.cxd4 exd4 { is again a transposition to our main line. } )
13. Re8( { A useful move, especially since White cannot yet play }14.d4 { due to }14...Bg4! { . } )
14. h3( 14.Be3?! { allows }14...d5! { . Now that the bishop is blocking the rook, and hence decreasing the pressure on the central point  e5 . } )
14. Be6{ Currently, we are well prepared against White's main plan:  d3 - d4 . }( 14...d5?! { would be premature. }15.exd5 Qxd5 16.Bb3 Qd6 17.Nh4!⩲ {  Nhf5  and  Qf3  are next, with pressure on the light squares. } )
15. Nh2
15. d5{ The initiative shifted to Black. }
16. exd5{ White played  Nh2  with the intention to build an attack on the kingside and therefore, it would be unlikely for him to suddenly exchange a lot of pieces with  exd5  and  Ne4 . }
16. Qxd5
17. Ne4{ Best, according to the engines. }
17. Nxe4
18. dxe4
18. Qxd1
19. Bxd1
