6. Qb3{ The most aggressive set-up - not hesitating to target the weak spot. }
6. Qd7{ We are poised to play ... Na5 . }
7. Nxc3( { After }7.Ng5 Nh6! { White already ran out of active moves. } )
7. Na5{ Taking the sting out of White's attack. }
8. Qb4
8. Nxc4
9. Qxc4
9. Ne7{ We have time to bring the knight to  g6 . On  f6 , it would have been vulnerable to the pawn assault  e4 - e5 . }
