9. Na5{ This is the Chigorin Variation of the Ruy Lopez. The knight is temporarily steered to the edge of the board. White can't avoid to lose their best minor piece, the light-squared bishop, so they spend time manoeuvring it from  Bb3  to  c2 . This allows Black to advance their c-pawn, gaining control of the queenside and disrupting White's plans to establish a strong center with  d2 - d4 . }
