12. dxe4
13. Nxe5
13. Nxe5{ We reach a position where two central pawns are hanging. }
14. dxe5
14. Nd7{ Not only trying to gain the pawn on  e5  back but also lurking for a possible 'supadupa' knight leap to  d3 ! }
15. e6
15. Ne5{ All we care for is the square on  d3 . }
16. exf7+
16. Kh8{ And nobody can change our minds! All our efforts are aimed at bringing the knight to  d3 , endorsing it by ... c7 - c5 - c4 . }( 16...Bxf7? 17.Qb1! { Suddenly, Black's empire is collapsing. }{ The  e4 -pawn is lost. }17...Nd3 18.Rd1± { . } )
17. Qc2
17. Nd3{ Arrived at the destination! }
18. Red1
18. c5{ The rest of the line gets quite complicated, but one thing is for sure: White has to shift gears! }( 19.Nxe4 Bxd1 20.Rxd1 { . Interestingly, White is going to sacrifice two rooks to encounter our dominant knight in the ensuing forced line. }20...c4! { White just can't cope with our  d3 -knight. }21.Rxd3 Qxd3 22.Qxd3 cxd3 { , when the position is double-edged. We will try to chase }{ the  b3 -bishop by ... Rfd8  and ... a6 - a5 - a4 , while opening files for our rooks on the queenside. } )
