9. Rb8{ Prophylaxis against both  a4  and  Nxf6  and  Bd5 . }
10. O-O
10. O-O{ We shouldn't act rashly by taking on  d5 . Instead, we complete our development first. }
11. d4( { We can handle }11.Be3 { without facing significant danger. }11...Nxd5 12.Bxd5 Bxe3 { The mass exchanges result in a balanced position. }13.fxe3 Ne7= { Anand had obtained equal chances in  Vachier Lagrave  (2775) -  Anand  (2764), ½-½ (34), Paris 2019. } )( 11.Bc2 Ba7 12.h3 Re8 ( 12...Be6 { is also playable. }13.Nxf6+ Qxf6 14.Be3 { , ½-½ (47),  Anton Guijarro  (2691) - Mamedyarov  (2759), chess24.com 2022. } )13.Be3 Nxd5 14.exd5 Bxe3 15.fxe3 Ne7 16.e4 Ng6= { Following with ... Bd7  and ... c6 , we obtain equal chances. } )( 11.h3 Nxd5 { Again, we can ease our task to equalise by swapping off the knight. }12.exd5 Ne7 13.d4 exd4 14.Nxd4 Bd7 15.Re1 Ng6⩱ { 1-0 (82),  Urazayev  (2451) -  Pichot    (2628), chess.com 2021. } )
11. Ba7{ The bishop is well positioned on the long diagonal. It exerts pressure on  d4  and  f2  (indirectly). }
12. Be3{ The position gets a sharp character with the two bishops opposing each other, apart from the  d4 -pawn. We have to take the consequences of  dxe5  into account on every move. }
12. Nxd5{ White built up the pressure, so we are not unhappy to have access to safe waters. }
