11. b6{ In this position, we are deviating from a game with an improvement. Black is setting up a wedge of pawns on the dark squares, restricting White as much as possible and halting the  d3 - d4  advance. }( 11...Qg4 { was a bit too enthusiastic to my taste. ½-½ (54),  Pichuaga  (2184) -  Dos Santos  (2065), Sao Jose de Rio Preto 2008. } )
12. a3
12. a5{ Stopping  b2 - b4 . }
13. Ne1
13. Ba6
14. b3
14. O-O-O{ White has nothing to play for since all the possible breaks (such as  d4 ,  b4 , and  f4 ) have been halted. }
