15. O-O-O{ White is in dire straits here. His king is too weak (a recipe for disaster) and the black pieces can hit their target from all angles. }( { Three regular moves which could come to (my) mind initially, are }16.Qf3 { , }16.f4 { , or }16.Rg1 { , all leading to a promising position (or more) for Black. } )
16. Qe2{ A difficult move to find and one which keeps White in the game. }( 16.Qxh5?! Kb8!→ { avoids the exchange of queens }{ through  Qf5  and leaves the white king endangered. } )( 16.Qf3 { brings the queen closer to the king, but loses immediately! }16...Bd6+ 17.Kh1 Nh4-+ { . } )( { Putting the rook on the g-file won't help White either: }16.Rg1 Bd6+!-+ { . } )
