5. exd4
6. cxd4
6. Bb4+( { Gaining an important tempo in order to instantly strike back in the center by ... d7 - d5 , or take the pawn on  e4 . White has now three main moves: }7.Nc3 { , }7.Nbd2 { , and }7.Bd2 { . Actually, all contain venom. } )
7. Nbd2{ This move is mostly played on the top level currently. }
7. Nxe4
8. d5{ With the board on fire and a space advantage for White, Black should be on qui vive. }
8. Nxd2{ Exchanging while being a pawn up. Straightforward and strong! }
9. Bxd2
9. Bxd2+
10. Qxd2
10. Ne7
11. h4( { A new attempt by no one less than  Caruana , although it was an internet blitz game and not the Candidates. }11.O-O-O d6 12.h4 { was the move order  Jorden van Foreest  chose in his game against  Navara  in 2022, leading to transposition to  11.h4 . } )
11. d6
12. h5
12. h6{ Obviously not allowing  h5 - h6 . }
13. O-O-O
13. O-O
14. Rdg1{ White's intentions are crystal clear. Thus, let's sabotage them for a while. }
14. Bg4{ I would like to propose this new move. The idea behind it will be revealed in a couple of moves. }( 14...c6? 15.g4! { is too dangerous. 1-0 (50)  J. van Foreest  (2714) -  Navara  (2700), chess24.com 2022. } )( 14...b5 { was played twice by two strong players. However, both had to undergo a tough attack. }15.Bb3 Bg4 16.Nh4 c5?! 17.f3 Bxh5 18.g4 Bg6 19.Nf5! f6 ( 19...Bxf5 20.gxf5 Nxf5 21.Bc2 Qd7 22.Bxf5 Qxf5 23.Qxh6+- { and there is no way to stop  Qxg7  or  Qh8  mate. } )20.Bc2 Kf7 21.Nxg7! { and it didn't take too much effort to gain the full point. 1-0 (49),  Caruana  (2792) -  Nakamura  (2736), chess.com 2022. } )
15. Rh4
15. Qd7{ Using the similar idea of setting up a battery along the  h7 - b1  diagonal. }
16. Qf4
16. Bf5{ Allowing  g2 - g4 - g5 , but relying on ... Qf5 . }
17. g4
17. Bh7
18. g5
18. Qf5{ The position remains complex, but at least we managed to exchange queens and our knight will land on  f5  and guard the  g7 -pawn. Hopefully, this position will be tested more in practice. }
