12. Ng6( { Forcing the repetition of moves. }12...O-O { leads to sharp play: }13.Rxf6 gxf6 14.Qd4 Ng6 15.Bh6 Re8 { , all forced moves. The position is unclear. Following }16.Bb5 { , Black is losing the exchange, as after }16...Bd7 { , }{ White would take on  f6 . }{    }16...Re5! { Improving the pawn structure. }17.Nxe5 fxe5 18.Qe3 { . }{ White aims for  f2 - f4 , finding a way to the black king. }18...Bd7! { First consolidating, before throwing in the pawn. }19.Bg5 Qe8 20.Bd3 f5 { , with unclear play in  J. van Foreest  (2688) -  Aronian  (2782), 1-0 (52), chess24.com 2021. } )
13. Re4+
13. Ne7{ And players could repeat or return to the main line. }
