9. d5{ By far the most challenging move. }
9. Bf6( { Mostly played and best, although }10...Ne5 { deserves consideration as well. } )
10. Re1( 10.dxc6? { This move was played over 80 times in my database, but it isn't good at all. }10...bxc6 11.Re1 O-O 12.Rxe4 d5∓ { , using the fork to win back the piece. } )
10. Ne7( { I deem }10...O-O { is slightly inaccurate, as it gives White the additional option of }11.Rxe4 Ne7 12.d6!?∞ { . } )
11. Rxe4
11. d6( 11...O-O 12.d6!?∞ { once again. } )
12. Bg5
12. Bxg5
13. Nxg5
13. h6{ The best move, asking the knight for clarification. Here we are on crossroads, as White has a wide palet of moves available. }( { I don't like the complications arising after }13...O-O 14.Nxh7! Kxh7 15.Qh5+ Kg8 16.Rh4 f5 17.Qh7+ Kf7 18.Rh6! { , }{ preparing for  Bc4 - e2 - h5 +, is quite alarming for us. } )
14. Qe2{ Preparing for the tripling on the e-file. }
14. hxg5{ We are entering a forced line, which should be studied thoroughly to know how to deal with the imminent threats. }
15. Re1
15. Be6( { A splendid defensive resource, blocking the e-file. Returning the piece would lead to a position in which we are tied down: }15...O-O 16.Rxe7 Bf5 17.Qh5!+- { . } )
16. dxe6
16. f6{ Keep the position and the  a1 -diagonal closed! The position is tense since White needs to find a breach in the dike while Black is intending to escape the danger zone with the king by means of ... c6 , (eventually ... d5 ), queen out to  b6  or  a5 , followed by long castling. }( 16...f5? { Opening the gates wouldn't be a good idea. }17.Rd4! { Prophylaxis against Black's key defensive idea }{ of ... c6  and ... d5 . }17...c6 { ( }17...O-O 18.Qd2 { and White found the breach in the dike. }18...f4 { and now the fifth rank lies open. }19.Rd5!! Nxd5 20.e7! { wins for White.)   }18.Qd2 d5 19.Qxg5! { We clearly see the difference between   }16...f6 { and }16...f5 { now. } )
17. Re3{ The most dangerous plan: swapping off the royal guard with  Rh3 . }
17. c6{ Still, two more moves to go before the king is secure. }
18. Rh3{ After the exchange of rooks,  Qh5 + is on the menu. }
18. Rxh3
19. gxh3{ How to keep the invader outside? }
19. g6{ Necessary to repel the devastating  Qh5 + threat, but now  f6  becomes a target. }
20. Qf3
20. Qa5{ And finally, we are safe due to the double threat of ... Qxe1 + and long castling. }( { Please refrain from }20...f5?? 21.Qc3! { , when Black is on the ropes. } )
21. Re2
21. Qf5{ Followed by long castling and ... d5 . }
