15. Na5{ After White's  13.bxc3 , guarding the  d4 -pawn, the bishop and knight don't function anymore. It makes sense to reroute the knight to greener pastures. Besides, the knight makes place for the redeployment of the bishop to  c7  by ... c7 - c6 . }
16. O-O
16. Rae8{ With the idea to play ... Nc4 . }( { The idea of bringing the knight to  c4  by }16...Nc4 { is premature, because of }17.Bxc4 Bxf3 ( 17...dxc4? 18.Ne5!  )18.Bd3! { ± }{ In contrast with the rook on  e8 , here ... Be4  is not possible. } )
17. Ne5
17. Bxe2
18. Qxe2
18. Qe6{ Preparing for ... Nc4  and anticipating on the pawn avalanche by  f2 - f4 ,  g2 - g4  and eventually  f4 - f5 . }
19. f4
19. Nc4{ Back on track. }
20. Rae1{ In my database, this position was reached 3 times. }
20. Nxe5{ Following  So  and  Kryvorucko  who both obtained a balanced position quite easily. }
21. fxe5{ This move hasn't been tested yet. }
21. c6{ Maybe White has a symbolic advantage here. The bishop will meddle again with internal affairs. }
