12. h3{ White has deferred for long from playing  h2 - h3 , pondering about its usefullness. He didn't opt for the queenside expansion by  b2 - b4  &  a2 - a4 , nor the quick advance in the center with  d3 - d4 .    Currently, he is out of useful plans apart from the central action with  d3 - d4 . To conduct this plan, he is after all forced to play  h2 - h3 , to stop ... Bg4 . }( 12.d4 Bg4! { Exerting maximum pressure on  d4 . }13.h3 Bxf3 14.Qxf3 exd4 15.Nf5 { , ½-½ (27),  Anand  (2770) -  Giri  (2782), Leuven 2016. }15...Ne5! { when }16.Qg3 { doesn't work, because of }16...Nh5!∓ { . } )
12. d5{ Choosing for the active instead of the symmetrical approach! }( 12...Re8 13.d4 { with a slight pull for White. } )
13. exd5
13. Nxd5( { We can't take back on  d5  with the pawn, unfortunately: }13...cxd5? 14.Nxe5 Nxe5 15.Rxe5± { . } )
{ White could better refrain from taking on  e5 . }14. Nxe5
14. Nxe5
15. Rxe5
15. Bxf2+{ A common tactic in the Italian! White's rook on  e5  is really awkward. }
16. Kxf2
16. Qf6+{ White loses everything. }
