7. Bg4{ This is not the main continuation, but the move ... Bg4  is approved by the strongest engines. }
8. Bb5{ White is abandoning the plan consisting of a kingside attack. Instead, he is aiming for a walk-over in the center. }
8. exd4{ As the temperature was rising revolving  e5 , this is the time to trade. }
9. cxd4
9. Nge7{ Completing development, relying on the next response against  d4 - d5 . }
10. d5
10. a6{ As it appears, White cannot win a piece. The good thing for us is that we have some pocket money in the shape of an extra pawn. }
11. Ba4
11. b5
12. dxc6
12. bxa4{ Losing our 'pocket money' - i.e. the extra pawn - but in return, we have the more active pieces. }
13. Qxa4
