5. d4{ In 2009, 13 years after I first encountered it, this system caught my attention once again when one of my students faced it. I was deeply impressed by it during my time playing in the B-group of Wijk aan Zee, where I had the opportunity to watch all the games of the A-group. Specifically, I vividly recall how the white player Sergei Movsesian expertly outplayed Michael Adams in a truly captivating manner. }
5. Bxd4( 5...exd4 6.e5! { is the famous Max Lange Attack. It's a sharp and aggressive option for White. After }6...d5 7.exf6 dxc4 { , they can choose between }8.fxg7 { and }8.Re1+ { . Theoretically, Black is doing fine against both, but I find our defensive task after  5...Bxd4  much easier. } )
