8. Be6{ There are other recent tries here, but I deem this one the most solid. Exchanging the strongest minor piece of our opponent. }( 8...Qe7 9.Na3 Bd7 { was tried by  Caruana  in an internet game. White could try }10.f5 { with a complicated position }{ , 1-0 (47),  Abdusattorov  (2627) -  Caruana  (2835), chess.com 2020. } )
9. fxe5
9. dxe5( 9...Bxc4? { is simply bad: }10.Qxd4 Bxf1 11.exf6+- { . } )
