10. Qe7
11. c3{ The 'main line' of this rare variation, according to Movsesian. }
11. Bxc4{ Given the fact that Black doesn't want to help the  a3 -knight to be improved to  c4  (and eventually  e3  and  f5 ), one ought to say that this is a bad move. The reason that I recommend it anyway, is that ... Ne6  followed by ... Qc5  will obstruct the knight's route. On top of that, the  e6 -knight blockades the f-file once it lands on  f4 . }( 11...Nc6?! { is still played in practice, as well by world-class players like  MVL  and  Dominguez  recently, but definitely not as convincing as  11...Bxc4  as we will see in the next lines: }12.Kh1 Rd8 ( 12...Bxc4 13.Nxc4± {  MVL  had a lot of problems to solve here, ½-½ (26),  Manu David  (2360) -  Vachier Lagrave  (2778), chess.com 2020. } )13.Qe2 h6 14.Bxf6 gxf6 15.Rf2 Rg8 16.Raf1 Rg6 17.Nc2 Kf8 18.Ne3± { . White is much better since Black cannot find shelter for the king. 1-0 (38),  Movsesian  (2751) -  Adams  (2712), Wijk aan Zee 2009. } )
12. Bxf6( 12.Nxc4 Ne6! { We are lifting the pin. White is forced to take because of the threat ... Qc5 +. }13.Bxf6 gxf6 { transposes to the text move. } )
12. gxf6{ Here we see White's compensation in the shape of our weakened pawn structure and king in the middle. Fortunately, the  a3 -knight has to take a long route to the fertile lands. }
13. Nxc4
13. Ne6{ White is planning to steer the knight via  e3  towards  d5  or  f5 . Black must do all within his powers to impede this plan while he still can. }( 13...Qc5?! 14.cxd4 Qxc4 15.Rc1 Qxd4+ 16.Qxd4 exd4 17.Rxc7 O-O 18.Rxf6⩲ { is slightly better for White, 1-0 (70),  Degraeve  (2561) - Bindrich  (2507), Germany 2010. } )
14. Kh1
14. Qc5{ The rescue for Black. Through this prophylaxis, White cannot conduct his knight manoeuvre via  e3  to  d5  or  f5 . }( 14...Rg8? { A small misstep with devastating effect. }15.Ne3± c6 { Impeding  Nd5 , but not  Nf5 . }16.Nf5 Qd7 17.Nd6+ Ke7 18.Nf5+! { followed by  Qh5 , was winning for White in  Geomerd  -  Westerhof , 1-0 (25), Hilversum 2022. } )
15. Qe2
15. Nf4{ White is forced to give up the exchange. }
