11. Bg7{ Indirectly hitting  b2 , preparing for castling. Our development is almost accomplished. }
12. Qd2{ White tries to take out his bishop before castling. The queen is misplaced since Black will harrass the queen with the next sequence of moves. }
12. Nf6
13. Qa5( { White cannot afford quitely developping his bishop, as the queen on  d2  will be prone to be chased by the black rook on  d8 : }13.Be2 dxe5! 14.fxe5 Rd8 15.Qe3 ( 15.exf6 Rxd2 16.fxe7 Rxb2-+ { Black is winning. } )15...Nd7∓ { The  e5 -pawn will be lost, after which White doesn't have any compensation. } )
13. O-O{ A great concept! We gain time by sacrificing our bishop, pursuing an attack on the king. }
14. Qxa6
14. dxe5{ Opening the position with White's king in the center. }
15. Be2( { The attack continues after }15.f5!? Qc5 { . } )( 15.fxe5 Ng4 { An avalanche of pieces is heading for White's king. } )
15. exf4
16. Nc3( 16.O-O Qe3+! 17.Kh1 Qxe2-+ { White is losing. } )
16. Ne4{ We are shelling at the enemy's king from all angles. }
17. Rc1
17. Qh4+{ Good game! }
