9. O-O( { I am less convinced by }9...d4 { . }10.Bg5 { The most popular choice on highest level. }O-O 11.Nd2 a5!? { This was tried by Giri, in order to block the pawn majority, and is a good alternative. }( 11...Bg4 12.Nf3 h6 13.Bxf6 Bxf6 14.h3 Be6 15.b4⩲ { Black's pawn is blocked, while White enjoys the majority on the queenside. 1-0 (39),  Shankland  (2708) -  Vidit  (2727), Kolkata 2021. } )12.Nb3 ( { Another way to go is }12.Re1 h6 13.Bh4 c5 { White puts some pressure across the e-file, though Black has some defensive resources. }14.Qf3 Ra6! { The rook lift makes that Black's control across the 6th rank is increased. }15.h3 Qc7∞ { Followed by ... Bb7 . } )12...h6 13.Bh4 g5!? { The position is getting very wild, which isn't my cup of tea. }14.Bg3 c5 { ½-½ (33),  Najer  (2635) -  Giri  (2780), Khanty-Mansiysk 2019. }{ Wild complications would have arisen after }15.f4!? { when ... Ng4  or ... Ra6  leads to highly unclear play. } )
10. Nc3
