7. Nf3( 7.Bxf7+ { loses a piece to }7...Kf8 8.f4 d6-+ { . } )
7. d5{ We have also passed the Rubicon river, and we can no longer keep our feet dry. We ought to play as active as possible! }
8. Bxd5
8. Bg4{ This strong bishop move, is the last active piece meddling with battle: the main part of our strategy. }
9. h3{ Lifting the pin with  h3  is dangerous. }
9. Bxf3
10. gxf3{ It is unclear how White can fend off all the threats. }
10. O-O-O( 10...Nh5!→ { is also strong. } )
11. Bb3
11. Nh5{ We are following the strong Russian GM and theoretician Alexander Motylev. }
12. d3{ 0-1 (46),  Paravyan  (2605) -  Motylev  (2651), Moscow 2019. }
12. Qh4
13. Rh2
13. Rd6{ White should throw in the towel. }
