13. Qe2+{ Taking control over the  e5 -square. }
13. Ne5{ A beautiful move, threatening mate on  f4 ! }( 13...Kd8? { looks like a logical move to defend  c7 , but it is a mistake. }{ After }14.fxg5 { , }{  f2  and  e5  are defended and the attack grinds to a standstill: }14...Qe5+ 15.Qxe5± { . } )
