10. Qe2( { After }10.Qe3 Bd6 { the queen is misplaced. For example, }11.O-O ? Bxh2+! 12.Kxh2 Ng4+ { . } )
10. Bd6{ White's king's position is troubling. Due to the pressure on  h2 , White can not castle easily. }
11. h3( { A good reaction to }11.d3 { is }11...O-O! { , simply ignoring the pawn. White would be foolish to open the position with }12.dxe4 { , because }12...Bg4 13.f3 Nxe4!! { is a nasty surprise. The queen meddles with the affairs. }14.fxg4 Qh4+ 15.Kf1 Rae8 { wins for Black. } )
11. O-O
12. O-O
12. Bf5{ White can no longer complete their development. 0-1 (30),  Flores Quillas  (2245) -  Gonzalez  (2049), chess.com 2021. }
