11. Nd7{ As we have already seen in our theory, this is called the Keres Defense. What is the idea? Bacrot wants to put the bishop on  f6  trying to increase the pressure on the  d4 -pawn while the knight on  d7  helps solidify the central pawns. }
12. Nbd2
12. exd4
13. cxd4
13. Nc6{ Black moves the knight back to the center to attack  d4 . }
14. d5{ The most popular choice for White here. }
14. Nce5
15. Nxe5
15. Nxe5
16. f4{ This is White's idea in these lines, trying to expel Black's knight from the center. }
16. Ng6{ These days there are a lot of subtleties here, some time ago in the past this setup by Black used to be considered a bit dubious but I'm happy to say that the Keres passes the engines test and my engines do like the position we are looking at now. }
17. Nf3
17. Bh4{ We must be precise with our moves here, and this is the way to go. }
