18. Na4{ This is the position black was targeting. It appears somewhat favorable, given the protected passed pawn on  c4 . However, it's important to note that white will launch an assault on the kingside, while our focus is on cultivating counterplay on the queenside. Hence, a closed position would be advantageous for white.    Merely doubling on the a-file neither displays finesse nor provides the necessary counterplay, as White can effortlessly barricade with  a3 . The move ... Na4  is a superior choice, hinting at potential ... Nc3  maneuvers in upcoming moves. }
19. a3{ Fortifying the pawns. }
