{ Welcome back to this video, where I cover a game against Daniël Stellwagen from the 2007 Tata Steel Challengers group in Wijk aan Zee.    Stellwagen was viewed as one of the standout prodigies of his era, alongside players like myself and Erwin L'ami. Being the youngest in our cohort, many believed he had the greatest potential. However, to the chess world's disappointment, he decided to step away from his chess career and pursue academia as a chemistry professor, which means we no longer have the pleasure of witnessing his games.    Nevertheless, our encounter in this game was intriguing, and I'm eager to share it with you. It offers valuable insights into the key strategies of the Ruy Lopez Chigorin. }1. e4
